# kAIxU SuperIDE — Deploy Notes

---

## MULTIPLE PROJECTS + ONE DATABASE

Yes. Multiple Netlify sites (or any app) can point at the same Neon database.
Just set the same DATABASE_URL in each project's Netlify env vars.
All data is separated at the application layer by org_id and user_id,
so projects don't bleed into each other. Works fine.

---

## STEP 1 — Neon Database

Go to https://console.neon.tech → your project → SQL Editor

### Enable pgvector (required for AI semantic search / embeddings)
Without this the /embeddings endpoint crashes on first use.

```sql
CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS vector;
```

### Run the schema (first time only)
Either paste the contents of sql/schema.sql into the SQL Editor,
or run locally:

```bash
node scripts/migrate.js
```

### Optional: Enable Row-Level Security
For production databases where you want Postgres-level tenant isolation
(in addition to the application-layer checks), run sql/rls.sql after schema.sql.
This adds per-row access policies to users, workspaces, orgs, and audit_logs.
Requires setting `SET LOCAL app.current_user_id = '<uuid>'` before queries.

```sql
-- Paste contents of sql/rls.sql into Neon SQL Editor
```

### Insert plan rows (required for billing to work)
Fill in your real Stripe price IDs before running:

```sql
INSERT INTO plans (name, ai_calls_limit, storage_gb, max_workspaces, max_members, stripe_price_id) VALUES
  ('free',       100,    1,   3,   1,  null),
  ('pro',        2000,   10,  20,  5,  'price_XXXX'),
  ('team',       10000,  50,  100, 25, 'price_XXXX'),
  ('enterprise', -1,     500, -1,  -1, 'price_XXXX');
```

