## STRIPE SETUP — FULL WALKTHROUGH

### Step A — Create Products in Stripe

Go to https://dashboard.stripe.com/products → Add product for each plan below.

**Product 1: kAIxU Pro**
- Name: kAIxU Pro
- Description: 2,000 AI calls/mo, 20 workspaces, 5 members, 10GB storage
- Pricing model: Recurring
- Price: $19.00 / month
- Save → copy the price ID (price_XXXX) → this is your PRO_PRICE_ID

**Product 2: kAIxU Team**
- Name: kAIxU Team
- Description: 10,000 AI calls/mo, 100 workspaces, 25 members, 50GB storage
- Pricing model: Recurring
- Price: $79.00 / month
- Save → copy the price ID → this is your TEAM_PRICE_ID

**Product 3: kAIxU Enterprise**
- Name: kAIxU Enterprise
- Description: Unlimited AI calls, unlimited workspaces, unlimited members, 500GB storage
- Pricing model: Recurring
- Price: custom / contact sales (set $499.00 as placeholder or use Stripe quotes)
- Save → copy the price ID → this is your ENTERPRISE_PRICE_ID

### Step B — Insert Plans into Neon

Replace the price_XXXX values with your real IDs from Step A, then run in Neon SQL Editor:

```sql
INSERT INTO plans (name, ai_calls_limit, storage_gb, max_workspaces, max_members, stripe_price_id) VALUES
  ('free',       100,    1,   3,   1,  null),
  ('pro',        2000,   10,  20,  5,  'price_XXXX'),
  ('team',       10000,  50,  100, 25, 'price_XXXX'),
  ('enterprise', -1,     500, -1,  -1, 'price_XXXX');
```

(-1 means unlimited in the codebase — quota checks treat -1 as no limit)

### Step C — Add Webhook

Stripe Dashboard → Webhooks → Add endpoint:
- URL: https://YOUR-SITE.netlify.app/.netlify/functions/stripe-webhook
- Events:
  - customer.subscription.created
  - customer.subscription.updated
  - customer.subscription.deleted
  - invoice.payment_succeeded
  - invoice.payment_failed
- Save → copy Signing Secret (whsec_...) → add to Netlify as STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET

### Step D — Stripe env vars to add to Netlify

| Variable              | Where to get it                                         |
|-----------------------|---------------------------------------------------------|
| STRIPE_SECRET_KEY     | Stripe Dashboard → Developers → API keys → Secret key   |
| STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET | Stripe Dashboard → Webhooks → your endpoint → signing secret |

Use sk_test_... and the test webhook secret while testing.
Switch to sk_live_... and a new live webhook when going live.

